### Key objects and their roles

| Object | Role |
|---|---|
| `UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken` | Carries credentials (unauthenticated) or principal+authorities (authenticated) |
| `SecurityContext` | Thin wrapper that holds the `Authentication` object |
| `SecurityContextHolder` | `ThreadLocal` store — makes auth accessible anywhere on current thread |
| `HttpSession` | Server-side persistent store for `SecurityContext` across requests |
| `JSESSIONID` | Cookie sent by browser — key to look up the right `HttpSession` |
| `UserDetails` | Spring's contract for your user object — bridge between your entity and Spring Security |
| `UserDetailsService` | Your code — queries DB, returns `UserDetails` |
| `DaoAuthenticationProvider` | Spring's code — orchestrates `UserDetailsService` + `PasswordEncoder` |
| `PasswordEncoder` | BCrypt — one-way hash comparison, never decrypts |
| `FilterChainProxy` | Entry point — passes every request through the security filter chain |

