### Production considerations worth mentioning

- **Externalize sessions to Redis** via `spring-session-data-redis` — otherwise sessions live in JVM heap, lost on restart, not shared across instances
- **Set session timeout** — `server.servlet.session.timeout=30m`
- **Secure cookie flags** — `http-only=true` (blocks JS access, prevents XSS stealing the cookie), `secure=true` (only sent over HTTPS)
- **Limit concurrent sessions** — `maximumSessions(1)` prevents one account being logged in from multiple places simultaneously
- **JWT for stateless APIs** — replaces session entirely, auth state lives in the token on the client side, no server-side session store needed
